newsitem.title: TUNISIA: Tunisian treasury rate falls at this week's sale.
newsitem.headline: Tunisian treasury rate falls at this week's sale.

text.p: The Tunisian Treasury on Tuesday said it sold 49.96 million dinars of three-year notes at its weekly auction on December 10, repaying maturing paper totalling 69.3 million dinars.
It sold three-year notes payable in equal annual tranches worth 15 million dinars at an 8.0-percent coupon rate, down from a 8.0625 percent at last week's auction.
It also sold 34.96 million dinars three-year note payable in equal annual tranche at 8.0625 percent.
Banks bid for 327.8 million dinars of three-, four-, five- and seven-year paper between 8.0 and 9.0 percent. ($=one dinar)
